quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  53,1,"By the star when it descends,"
  53,2,"Your companion [i.e., Muḥammad] has not strayed, nor has he erred,"
  53,3,"Nor does he speak from [his own] inclination."
  53,4,"It is not but a revelation revealed,"
  53,5,"Taught to him by one intense in strength [i.e., Gabriel] -"
  53,6,"One of soundness.<sup foot_note=197440>1</sup> And he rose to [his] true form<sup foot_note=197439>2</sup>",footnotes:197440:1,footnotes:197439:2
  53,7,"While he was in the higher [part of the] horizon.<sup foot_note=197441>1</sup>",footnotes:197441:1
  53,8,"Then he approached and descended"
  53,9,"And was at a distance of two bow lengths or nearer."
  53,10,"And he revealed to His Servant<sup foot_note=197442>1</sup> what he revealed [i.e., conveyed].",footnotes:197442:1